  OFFLOAD file [offset] [/L|Q]

This external command displays the
structure of a DOS loadable file. It
shows the start and end address, and
the file position of each segment
(after the header) as hexadecimal
number.

With the /L option, the file is also
loaded into memory. With /Q, you are
asked before each segment is loaded.
If an offset is specified, it will be
added to the load address of every
segment. The offset must be specified
as hexadecimal numbers.

